bug.short_desc: preinstalled shortcut to launch the application do not work
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem:
The FMW installer is somehow improperly creating the shortcut for launching FMW. It fails to launch from the list of applications and from cortana. It can be launched directly in from Program Files x86 folder however.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): https://github.com/MartinBriza/MediaWriter/releases/download/4.0.95/FedoraMediaWriter-win32-4.0.95.exe
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Use Cortana search or Windows icon (lower left) to alphabetically find Fedora Media Writer and launch 2. 3.
Actual results:
Cortana: Two dialogs one after the other (attached). Windows icon, alphabetical program listing: Only the 2nd dialog.
Expected results:
Should just launch either way.
Additional info:

Created attachment 1273060 first dialog
First dialog that appears, only when using Cortana/search then selecting FMW.

Created attachment 1273061 second dialog
Using Cortana this is the 2nd dialog that appears.
Using Windows icon, alphabetical program listing this is the only dialog that appears.
This is now fixed upstream, there was a mistake in the link that's installed to the Start menu.
